DOCUMENT();

loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
           "MathObjects.pl",
           );

TEXT(beginproblem());

Context("Numeric");
Context()->strings->add( none => {} );

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$d = non_zero_random(-5,2,1)+7;
$n = random(2,9,1);


$m = 1;
$k = $d*$n;

BEGIN_TEXT
If possible write the following expression in $BBOLD slope-intercept $EBOLD form.

\[ \frac{y-x}{ $d } = $n \]

$PAR
a) What is the value of \( m\) when written in slope-intercept form?  If the equation cannot be written in slope-intercept form, enter ${BBOLD}none$EBOLD in the box.
$BR
\(m =  \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}
$PAR
b) What is the value of \(b\) when written in slope-intercept form?  If the equation cannot be written in slope-intercept form, enter ${BBOLD}none$EBOLD in the box.
$BR
\( b = \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}

END_TEXT

ANS( Compute($m)->cmp() );
ANS( Compute($k)->cmp() );

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR
$BBOLD SOLUTION $EBOLD
$PAR
Rewriting in slope-intercept form:
\[ \frac{y-x}{ $d } = $n \]
$BR
\[ y - x = ($n)($d) \]
$BR
\[ y = x + $k \]

END_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();
